# =============================================================================
# CafeMatch Web Client — Environment Variables (TEMPLATE)
# =============================================================================
# Copy this file to `.env.development.local` (for local dev, gitignored) or
# `.env.production` (for production builds), then fill in real values.
#
# Vite only exposes vars prefixed with VITE_ to the browser. Anything else
# stays server-side and won't reach the bundle.
#
# Files Vite loads, in order of priority (later overrides earlier):
#   .env                        — committed defaults
#   .env.local                  — gitignored, all envs
#   .env.[mode]                 — committed, mode-specific (development/production)
#   .env.[mode].local           — gitignored, mode-specific (recommended for secrets)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------


# ── Google AdSense ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Used by [src/components/InFeedAd.tsx](src/components/InFeedAd.tsx) to serve
# in-feed ads in HomePage / TrendingPage. Leave empty in dev — the component
# will render a "Sponsored slot" placeholder instead of pinging AdSense.
#
# Get these from https://adsense.google.com/ once your site is approved:
#   1. AdSense Console → Account → Account information → copy Publisher ID
#   2. AdSense Console → Ads → By ad unit → Create In-feed ad → copy Slot ID
#
# In dev mode, `data-adtest=on` is auto-injected so AdSense returns test creatives
# ("Test Ad — Do Not Click"). Never click your own ads — instant ban.
 

# Force AdSense test mode in production (e.g. while QA-testing a release build).
# Leave commented out for normal prod — real ads should serve.
VITE_ADSENSE_CLIENT=
VITE_ADSENSE_INFEED_SLOT=
